Quote:  Mr Dollar, a cartoon character resembling a bank note, was a critical part of the Government's nationwide campaign to inform New Zealanders of the currency changeover. Able to relate to New Zealanders of all ages and backgrounds, Mr Dollar led the successful changeover to the decimal currency on July 10 1967.
